","content":"**Value formatting**: You can supply a function to format each value; if you don't, the tooltip shows the point's `y` (or nothing when null). Use the formatter for custom data shapes."},"802":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#internal-component","content":"This component is **internal-only** and not exported from the package. It is intended for use inside chart components."},"803":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#props","content":"The `Tooltip` component accepts the following props:"},"804":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-14","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"**Default:** When `formatValue` is not provided, the tooltip uses a formatter that reads the data point’s `y` property (same as the chart's default Y accessor), converts it to a string, and returns an empty string for null. This is correct for the default `DataPoint` shape (`{ x, y }`)."},"805":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-15","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"**Custom:** Pass `formatValue` to control display. The function receives the datum and returns a string. Use it to both extract and format (e.g. currency, percentage, custom units). For custom data point shapes (generic `TooltipProps<YourDatum>`), you must pass `formatValue` because the default only reads `y`."},"806":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-16","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#single-series","content":"Basic tooltip with a single series and default formatting."},"807":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-17","page_id":"/do